Member Data Documentation

const u8 XHwIcap_ClbLut::CONFIG[4][2][2][2]

SHIFT_CONFIG, RAM_CONFIG, or LUT_CONFIG. Indexed by the slice (0-3). And then indexed by the logic element (LUT.F or LUT.G). Note that if the F LUT is in any sort of ram or shifter modes, the G LUT must also be in ram or shifter mode. Also, be sure to set the MODE bit appropriately.

const u8 XHwIcap_ClbLut::CONTENTS[4][2][16][2]

LUT memory contents. Indexed by slice first (0-3) and by XHI_CLB_LUT_F or XHI_CLB_LUT_G second.

const u8 XHwIcap_ClbLut::LUT_CONFIG[2]

Set CONFIG to LUT.

const u8 XHwIcap_ClbLut::LUT_MODE[1]

MODE resource values. Set MODE to LUT mode

const u8 XHwIcap_ClbLut::MODE[4][1][2]

RAM_MODE, ROM_MODE, or LUT_MODE. Indexed by the slice (0-3). If only one LUT is in RAM or SHIFT mode, it MUST be the G LUT.

const u8 XHwIcap_ClbLut::RAM_CONFIG[2]

Set CONFIG to ram.

const u8 XHwIcap_ClbLut::RAM_MODE[1]

Set MODE to RAM mode.

const u8 XHwIcap_ClbLut::ROM_MODE[1]

Set MODE to ROM mode. (Same as LUT mode)

const u8 XHwIcap_ClbLut::SHIFT_CONFIG[2]

CONFIG resource values. Set CONFIG to shfiter.
